ul.li: Maintain blood pressure below 130/80 mmHg through lifestyle modifications.
Limit daily sodium intake to less than 2.3 grams to support blood pressure control.
Engage in at least 150 minutes of moderate-intensity aerobic physical activity per week.
Achieve a body mass index (BMI) less than 25 kg/m2 to aid in blood pressure control.
Patient will implement and maintain a diabetes self-management plan to delay or prevent progression to type 2 diabetes.
Maintain hemoglobin A1c below 6.5% to reduce risk of progression to diabetes.
Maintain fasting plasma glucose below 7.0 mmol/L.
Achieve and maintain at least 5% weight loss from baseline to improve glycemic parameters.
Maintain blood pressure below 130/80 mm[Hg] to reduce cardiovascular and renal risk.
